When I was young, my mother sent me to Sunday School as punishment for trying to steal her car. I was only seven. I could barely reach the pedals. It was a set-up. The priest, or whoever it was, stood in front of me with a shotgun in one hand and a Bible in the other and recited chapter 13 of the Book of Revelation while I cowered on the floor. When I say recited, I obviously mean screamed. Later, when I grew up and the scars had healed, it occurred to me that chapter 13 might have been written...